abstract: >
  opendesk is an open-source desktop automation framework that gives AI models
  (Claude, GPT-4, and others) eyes and hands on the desktop via the Model Context
  Protocol (MCP). It provides screenshot capture with Set-of-Marks overlays,
  mouse and keyboard control, UI element interaction via accessibility APIs,
  clipboard access, OCR, and learn/replay task recording.
